data.name: label61.Text
data.value:
How does it work: Have GCode with Tx M6 commands for tool change. During streaming to grbl (on Arduino or other controller), the tool change command will be interpreted by GRBL-Plotter and script gcode will be inserted:
Notice 'Tx' command, get tool number 'x' Read tool change coordinates for tool number 'x' into variables TOAX, TOAY, TOAZ from actual tool table.
Notice 'M6' command If tool is in spindle insert script-code 'REMOVE' (use here TOLX,Y,Z for last tool coordinates) Insert script-code 'SELECT' into send-queue (use here TOAX,Y,Z tool coordinates) Insert script-code 'PICK UP' Insert script-code 'PROBE' Copy actual tool coordinates (TOAX,Y,Z to last coord. TOLX,Y,Z) Remove 'M6' from send queue, because grbl can't handle this command.

Setup window must be closed to use Gamepad in GUI.
